hpicfDSnoopV6.name: hpicfDSnoopV6

revisions.description: Importing hpicfSaviObjectsBindingEntry and hpicfSaviObjectsPortEntry from HPICF-SAVI-MIB and augmenting them instead of saviObjectsBindingEntry and saviObjectsPortEntry. Updated hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerStatus mib to specify not supported row status states.
Changed syntax type for hpicfDSnoopV6VlanEnable from OctetString to Vidlist.

hpicfDSnoopV6.contactinfo: Hewlett-Packard Company 8000 Foothills Blvd. Roseville, CA 95747
hpicfDSnoopV6.description: This MIB module contains HP proprietary objects for managing DHCPV6 Snooping.

hpicfDSnoopV6Enable.name: hpicfDSnoopV6Enable
hpicfDSnoopV6Enable.description: This object provides the administrative status of the DHCPv6 Snooping feature. This status must be enabled for DHCPv6 snooping to work.

hpicfDSnoopV6VlanEnable.name: hpicfDSnoopV6VlanEnable
hpicfDSnoopV6VlanEnable.description: This object contains vid map for vlans on which DHCPV6 Snooping is enabled. A bit that is on (equal to 1) indicates that DHCPV6 snooping is enabled on corresponding vlan .

hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseFile.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseFile
hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseFile.description: A location to store the lease database or to retrieve it after a reboot. The location must be given in the form of a Uniform Resource Locator (URL) as defined in RFC 2396. The permissible character sets and the encoding rules defined in RFC 2396 section 2 apply.

hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseWriteDelay.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseWriteDelay
hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseWriteDelay.description: The number of seconds to delay writing the DHCPv6 lease database file after a database change. This allows grouping multiple database changes into a single write. The default value is 300 seconds.

hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseWriteTimeout.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseWriteTimeout
hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseWriteTimeout.description: The number of seconds to wait for the database file transfer to finish. If file transfer is not over within this period, a file transfer failure message is displayed. To continue trying indefinitely, specify a value of 0. The default value is 300 seconds.

hpicfDSnoopV6OutOfResourcesTrapCtrl.name: hpicfDSnoopV6OutOfResourcesTrapCtrl
hpicfDSnoopV6OutOfResourcesTrapCtrl.description: This object provides the operational status of DSNOOPv6 out of resource control trap. The default value is enabled. This notification trap is sent when the number of bindings exceed the maximum limit of 8192 bindings. Configuration of this object requires SNMPv3 authentication.

hpicfDSnoopV6ErrantReplyTrapCtrl.name: hpicfDSnoopV6ErrantReplyTrapCtrl
hpicfDSnoopV6ErrantReplyTrapCtrl.description: This object provides the operational status of DSNOOPv6 errant repy control trap. The default value is enabled. This notification trap is sent when a DHCPv6 reply packet is received on an untrusted port or from an un-authorized server. Configuration of this object requires SNMPv3 authentication.

hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseFTPort.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseFTPort
hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseFTPort.description: A location to store the port value of the FT Server. The default port value will be 69 for TFTP and 22 for SFTP.

hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseSFTPUsername.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseSFTPUsername
hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseSFTPUsername.description: A location to store the Username of the SFTP Server. The default value of username is root.

hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseSFTPPassword.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseSFTPPassword
hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseSFTPPassword.description: A location to store the Password of the SFTP Server.

hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseValidateSFTPServer.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseValidateSFTPServer
hpicfDSnoopV6DatabaseValidateSFTPServer.description: This object sets the validate-sftp-server flag. When enabled, the user must login to the SFTP server to verify and accept the public key of the server. When disabled, the public key is accepted automatically.

hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerTable.name: hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerTable
hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerTable.description: Table of authorized DHCP server addresses.

hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerEntry.name: hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerEntry
hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerEntry.description: A row in the table, containing the address of a single authorized DHCP server.

hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerAddrType.name: hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerAddrType
hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerAddrType.description: The IP address type of authorized DHCPv6 server.

hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerAddress.name: hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerAddress
hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerAddress.description: The address of a known valid DHCP server. The type of address contained in this object is indicated by hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerAddrType. To allow a server packet to be forwarded to a client, it must be received on a trusted port from a server address in this table. If this table is empty, all addresses are trusted. Note that this feature compares the source address of the received DHCPv6 server packet against the addresses in this table. Therefore, this table must contain trusted server addresses and trusted DHCPv6 relays that a server packet may be relayed through.

hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerStatus.name: hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerStatus
hpicfDSnoopV6AuthorizedServerStatus.description: The status of this DHCP server address entry. Only 'active' entries are used when validating DHCP server packets. Row statuses createAndWait(5), notReady(3) and notInService(2) are not supported.

hpicfDSnoopV6CSForwards.name: hpicfDSnoopV6CSForwards
hpicfDSnoopV6CSForwards.description: Number of snooped DHCPv6 packets that were successfully forwarded from untrusted client ports towards trusted DHCPv6 server ports.

hpicfDSnoopV6CSMACMismatches.name: hpicfDSnoopV6CSMACMismatches
hpicfDSnoopV6CSMACMismatches.description: Number of snooped DHCPv6 client packets that were discarded due to MAC verification check failure.

hpicfDSnoopV6CSBadReleases.name: hpicfDSnoopV6CSBadReleases
hpicfDSnoopV6CSBadReleases.description: Number of snooped DHCPv6 client packets that were discarded because they were RELEASE packets received on a port different from the port that the address was leased to.

hpicfDSnoopV6CSUntrustedDestPorts.name: hpicfDSnoopV6CSUntrustedDestPorts
hpicfDSnoopV6CSUntrustedDestPorts.description: Number of snooped DHCPv6 client unicast packets that were discarded because they were destined to untrusted ports.

hpicfDSnoopV6SCForwards.name: hpicfDSnoopV6SCForwards
hpicfDSnoopV6SCForwards.description: Number of snooped DHCPv6 packets that were successfully forwarded from trusted DHCPv6 server ports to untrusted client ports.

hpicfDSnoopV6SCUntrustedPorts.name: hpicfDSnoopV6SCUntrustedPorts
hpicfDSnoopV6SCUntrustedPorts.description: Number of snooped DHCPv6 server packets that were dropped because they were received on untrusted ports.

hpicfDSnoopV6SCRelayReplyUntrustedPorts.name: hpicfDSnoopV6SCRelayReplyUntrustedPorts
hpicfDSnoopV6SCRelayReplyUntrustedPorts.description: Number of relay reply packets that were dropped by the switch because they were received on untrusted ports.

hpicfDSnoopV6SCUnauthorizedServers.name: hpicfDSnoopV6SCUnauthorizedServers
hpicfDSnoopV6SCUnauthorizedServers.description: Number of snooped DHCPv6 server packets that were discarded because they were received from unauthorized DHCPv6 server

hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileWriteAttempts.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileWriteAttempts
hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileWriteAttempts.description: Number of attempts that have been made to write the DHCPv6 lease database to a configured file location.

hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileWriteFailures.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileWriteFailures
hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileWriteFailures.description: Number of times that an attempt to write the DHCPv6 lease database to a configured file location has failed.

hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileReadStatus.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileReadStatus
hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileReadStatus.description: This object indicates whether the DHCPv6 lease database from configured location is loaded successfully after the last reboot.

hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileWriteStatus.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileWriteStatus
hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileWriteStatus.description: This object indicates whether the DHCPv6 lease database is currently synchronized with the the configured file server. 'notConfigured' means that the switch is not configured with a server location. 'delaying' means the switch is waiting for the write delay to expire before writing the current database. 'inProgress' means that a lease database transfer is active. 'succeeded' means that all leases in our database have been written to the server. 'failed' means that the last attempt to write our lease database failed.

hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileLastWriteTime.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileLastWriteTime
hpicfDSnoopV6DBFileLastWriteTime.description: Time at which the switch last successfully wrote the lease database to the server. This object contains a value of all zeroes if lease database is not written since the last reboot.

hpicfDSnoopV6MaxbindPktsDropped.name: hpicfDSnoopV6MaxbindPktsDropped
hpicfDSnoopV6MaxbindPktsDropped.description: This object provides the total number of DHCPv6 snooping packets dropped by the switch. A switch drops the DHCPv6 snooping packets on a port when the port exceeds maximum binding limit configured on it.

hpicfDSnoopV6ClearStats.name: hpicfDSnoopV6ClearStats
hpicfDSnoopV6ClearStats.description: This object clears the DSNOOPv6 statistics when set to TRUE. A write operation of FALSE leads to a no operation and a get request for this object always returns FALSE.

hpicfDSnoopV6PortMaxBindingTable.name: hpicfDSnoopV6PortMaxBindingTable
hpicfDSnoopV6PortMaxBindingTable.description: This table contains the maximum binding information of port.

hpicfDSnoopV6PortMaxBindingEntry.name: hpicfDSnoopV6PortMaxBindingEntry
hpicfDSnoopV6PortMaxBindingEntry.description: The maximum number of bindings on the Port.

hpicfDSnoopV6PortStaticBinding.name: hpicfDSnoopV6PortStaticBinding
hpicfDSnoopV6PortStaticBinding.description: This object indicates the static bindings configured on this port.

hpicfDSnoopV6PortDynamicBinding.name: hpicfDSnoopV6PortDynamicBinding
hpicfDSnoopV6PortDynamicBinding.description: This object indicates the number of dynamic bindings on this port.

hpicfDSnoopV6StaticBindingTable.name: hpicfDSnoopV6StaticBindingTable
hpicfDSnoopV6StaticBindingTable.description: This table contains the VLAN ID for binding entry.

hpicfDSnoopV6StaticBindingEntry.name: hpicfDSnoopV6StaticBindingEntry
hpicfDSnoopV6StaticBindingEntry.description: Extension of VLAN ID in hpicfSaviObjectsBindingTable.

hpicfDSnoopV6BindingVlanId.name: hpicfDSnoopV6BindingVlanId
hpicfDSnoopV6BindingVlanId.description: The VLAN on which this client is discovered.

hpicfDSnoopV6BindingLLAddress.name: hpicfDSnoopV6BindingLLAddress
hpicfDSnoopV6BindingLLAddress.description: The VLAN on which this client is discovered.

hpicfDSnoopV6BindingSecVlan.name: hpicfDSnoopV6BindingSecVlan
hpicfDSnoopV6BindingSecVlan.description: The secondary VLAN on which this client is discovered. if binding is learned on primary or normal VLAN, this object will be zero.

hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingOutOfResources.name: hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingOutOfResources
hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingOutOfResources.description: This trap indicates that the number of bindings exceeded the maximum limit of 8192 bindings. This notification trap is controlled by the state of ' hpicfDSnoopV6OutOfResourcesTrapCtrl' object. Implementation of this trap is optional.

hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingPort.name: hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingPort
hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingPort.description: The port of failed binding entry. Maximum binding limit is reached.

hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingMacAddress.name: hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingMacAddress
hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingMacAddress.description: The MAC address of failed binding entry. Maximum binding limit is reached.

hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingIpAddressType.name: hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingIpAddressType
hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingIpAddressType.description: The IPv6 address type of failed binding entry. Maximum binding limit is reached.

hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingIpAddress.name: hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingIpAddress
hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingIpAddress.description: The IPv6 address of failed binding entry. Maximum binding limit is reached.

hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingVlan.name: hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingVlan
hpicfDsnoopV6SourceBindingVlan.description: The VLAN of failed binding entry. Maximum binding limit is reached.

hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantReply.name: hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantReply
hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantReply.description: An hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantReply notification signifies that the DHCPV6 snooping entity has detected and dropped an errant DHCPv6 reply packet. This notification trap is controlled by the state of 'hpicfDSnoopV6ErrantReplyTrapCtrl' object

hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingNotifyCount.name: hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingNotifyCount
hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingNotifyCount.description: A count of the DHCPV6 snooping notification sent from the DHCPv6 snooping entity to the SNMP entity. This count may be greater than the count of notifications actually transmitted by the SNMP entity due to rate limiting or configuration.

hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantSrcMAC.name: hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantSrcMAC
hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantSrcMAC.description: The MAC address received in the errant DHCPv6 reply packet.

hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantSrcIPTyp.name: hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantSrcIPType
hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantSrcIPTyp.description: The type of address reported in hpicfDhcpSnoopSourceBindingErrantSrcIP.

hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantSrcIP.name: hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantSrcIP
hpicfDSnoopV6SourceBindingErrantSrcIP.description: The IPv6 address received in the errant DHCPv6 reply packet.

hpicfDSnoopV6BaseGroup.name: hpicfDSnoopV6BaseGroup
hpicfDSnoopV6BaseGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring and monitoring the base DHCPv6 snooping functionality.

hpicfDSnoopV6ServersGroup.name: hpicfDSnoopV6ServersGroup
hpicfDSnoopV6ServersGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring and monitoring DHCP snooping trusted servers.

hpicfDSnoopV6DbaseFileGroup.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DbaseFileGroup
hpicfDSnoopV6DbaseFileGroup.description: A collection of objects for configuring and monitoring DHCP snooping database file management.

hpicfDSnoopV6MaxBindingsGroup.name: hpicfDSnoopV6MaxBindingsGroup
hpicfDSnoopV6MaxBindingsGroup.description: A collection of objects for monitoring the binding limits on a port.

hpicfDSnoopV6StaticBindingsGroup.name: hpicfDSnoopV6StaticBindingsGroup
hpicfDSnoopV6StaticBindingsGroup.description: A collection of objects used to configure static binding for a VLAN.

hpicfDSnoopV6ClearStatsOptionsGroup.name: hpicfDSnoopV6ClearStatsOptionsGroup
hpicfDSnoopV6ClearStatsOptionsGroup.description: A collection of objects used to clear DSNOOPv6 statistics.

hpicfDSnoopV6TrapObjectsGroup.name: hpicfDSnoopV6TrapObjectsGroup
hpicfDSnoopV6TrapObjectsGroup.description: A collection of objects used in the DSNOOPv6 notification.

hpicfDSnoopV6TrapsGroup.name: hpicfDSnoopV6TrapsGroup
hpicfDSnoopV6TrapsGroup.description: A collection of trap objects that provide DSNOOPv6 notifications.

hpicfDSnoopV6DbaseFileGroup1.name: hpicfDSnoopV6DbaseFileGroup1
hpicfDSnoopV6DbaseFileGroup1.description: A collection of objects for configuring and monitoring DHCP snooping database file management.

hpicfDSnoopV6Compliance2.name: hpicfDSnoopV6Compliance2
hpicfDSnoopV6Compliance2.description: The compliance statement for HP Routing switches that support DHCPv6 Snooping.

hpicfDSnoopV6Compliance.name: hpicfDSnoopV6Compliance
hpicfDSnoopV6Compliance.description: The compliance statement for HP Routing switches that support DHCPv6 Snooping.
